title: Add Codex login/logout/status commands and setup flow
---
## Requirements

- Extend the CLI auth/config UX so users can sign in with a ChatGPT subscription and inspect or clear stored Codex credentials.
- Add a guided setup path in the config wizard (or equivalent onboarding flow) for choosing Codex subscription auth versus API key auth.
- Update validation/status output so Codex-backed providers report meaningful readiness without relying on `/models` API-key checks.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Users can initiate login, inspect status, and log out/remove stored Codex credentials from the CLI.
- Setup flow explains local-browser versus remote/headless login behavior.
- Validation output distinguishes API-key providers from Codex subscription providers.
